  "prompt": "What do you do if you love a girl but she is in a relationship with someone else?",
  "response": "Here are some healthy ways to handle this situation:\n\n1. Respect her current relationship\n- Do not try to interfere or break them up\n- Accept her current commitment to her partner\n\n2. Create emotional distance\n- Limit contact if possible\n- Avoid spending too much time together\n- Focus on healing and moving on\n\n3. Process your feelings\n- Talk to friends or a counselor\n- Allow yourself to feel sad\n- Practice self-care\n\n4. Work on yourself\n- Pursue personal goals and interests\n- Develop new hobbies\n- Meet new people\n- Build your self-confidence\n\n5. Consider dating other people\n- Be open to new romantic possibilities\n- Don't wait around hoping she'll become available\n\n6. If her relationship ends naturally\n- Wait a reasonable amount of time\n- Approach her respectfully\n- Be prepared that she might not be interested\n\n7. If feelings persist and are causing significant distress\n- Seek professional counseling\n- Learn healthy emotional management techniques\n\nRemember: True love means wanting the best for the other person, even if that doesn't include you romantically.",
